Next up is the Loudon classic, pretty cool being up here for this historic race ripping with some fast company and learning a new track, the paycheck is a big one and we’re all hungry for it. This weekend I’ll be ripping a Pirobon X80 with a Ducati 848 motor which is a work of art. Couldn’t be more stoked and privileged to ride it. Many many thanks to @bouldermotorsports and  #larrabureframing for making this weekend posible and letting me rip this machine. @pirellimotousa for the big support this weekend as well. And thanks to  @tytlerscycleracing for letting me come out and rip with the locals. 

@fastglass.media always killing the 📽️📽️

Happy Father’s Day to the crew chief that got us were we at today @ratamb . My dad has gone above and beyond to make sure the wheels were spinning and the podiums continue to happen. Happy Father’s Day and thank you for everything hope you enjoy your day! Much love pops!

We got penalized on the SuperSport class because we tested the hooligan bike Monday Tuesday so my penalty was sit out all of Q1, ready to go send it this morning in Q2.

@pittrace was sick this year, being able to win a SuperSport race head to head against the best in the usa has been a long time dream. Thank you @tytlerscycleracing for keeping me out there, and all sponsors that make this possible. Looking forward to end the season strong 💪❤️‍🔥

At the beginning of the year @daineseofficial came onboard to provide me with the best airbag leathers, boots and gear in the industry to keep me safe and ripping. This past weekend the boys @reallouisortega and @dainesemiami  surprised me with my first custom AXIAL D1  boots and they are hot ❤️‍🔥🔥. Forsure my good luck boots that helped me get the win on Saturday. Appreciate the help and support and of course keeping me safe at all times 🙏 

📸@fastglass.media thanks for taking you valuable time to get these done 🫶🫶

Few weeks back we went back to the roots and we went to rip with the @asrarace family, it was a blast going back to ride my zx10 on my @pirellimotousa to burn up some tires 💨 and just have fun on the bikes and that was accomplished forsure. We even lowered the @summitpointmp track record by just a few tenths. Thanks to the boys for the help around the pits. Can’t wait for more big bike action 🫶
